  # Employee Database Manager
 
  ## Table of Contents

  - [Installation](#installation)
  - [Usage](#usage)
  - [Contribution](#contribution)
  - [Tests](#tests)
  - [License](#license)
  - [Questions](#questions)
  ## Description
A node application that uses postgres to manage and alter and employee database. The program allows users to view departments, roles, and employees. It also allows for adding new employees, roles, and update employee roles.

  ## Installation
Install node and include the inquirer and pg packages using "npm i"  and "npm run build".

  ## Usage
In the terminal type: "psql - postgres". Then type your password. After that type" \i db/schema.sql" and "\i db/seeds.sql" to create and seed your employee database. Once that is complete type "\q" to quit. Then start the application by running "npm start". Follow the prompts to view and alter your database.

Video demonstration: [Video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_TkBhGIfo0)

